Mortgage calculator

High level input and output

	Input will be:
		1. Loan amount
		2. Annual Percentage rate (interest rate)
		3. Loan duration

	Output will be:
	1. monthly interest rate
	2. loan duration in months

Formula for Monthly Payment = 
m = p * (j / (1 - (1 + j)**(-n)))

m = monthly payment
p = loan amount
j = monthly interest rate
n = loan duration in months

	Rules and edges : 
	Loan amount will always be a positive integer.
	APR will be a positive float
	Duration will be for 5, 15, 30 years

	Test case - 
Input:	
Loan amount 100,000
APR - 5%
Loan length - 30 years

Output:
Monthly payment - $536.82


if [",", "$", "%", "."].include?($loan_amount.to_i) == true
